LAGOS – Covenant University, Ota, Ogun State, has emerged as the nation’s number-one uni­versity in the Times Higher Education (THE) Young Uni­versity Rankings 2022. Also, occupying the sec­ond and third positions on the rankings released on Wednesday are the Universi­ty of Ilorin (UNILORIN) and the Lagos State University (LASU). It would be recalled that LASU ranked third this year and was rated first in 2021 while Covenant University occupied the second position. FCT Council Poll: Abuja Indigenes Commend INEC, Minister For… VSF Launches Food Distribution To Victims Of Terrorism In Yobe The THE Young University Rankings list the world’s best universities that are 50 years old or younger and featured 539 universities, up from 475 in 2021. For the current rankings, 251 institutions are listed with “Reporter” status, meaning that they provided data but did not meet the el­igibility criteria to receive a rank. In the 2022 rankings, Cove­nant was rated within 201-250, UNILORIN 401+ while LASU occupied the third place.